&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Actually it does, as it was explained to me when I was SP in the Navy: You are allowed to use as much force as necessary to subdue your opponent, but not use greater than what they demonstrate.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;To explain, if a person has a knife, you are justified in knifing him, but not shooting him, if he has a gun, you are justified in shooting him. if he has no weapon at all, basically you are not allowed to shoot, OR knife him.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
