      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Yep I know all about reasonable force - I use it every single day (UK Police) - your definition is virtually the same as our law (well its actually three laws - Common Law, Criminal Law Act 1967 and Police and Criminal Evidence Act 1984) - all three govern the use of 'reasonable' force and when force can be used (the last Act - PACE 1984 is only useable by Police Officers).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It just boggles my mind that that you can have a legal system where someone can file a claim against&amp;nbsp;a person&amp;nbsp;defending themselves. I obviously don't know the full ins and outs of the case but hitting someone that is holding a gun to you with a pipe seems very reasonable in the circumstances.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Murril Merryweather&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
